    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Maximum Security Adolescent</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>James A Messina letter on Margaret Talbot's September 10 article says he supports 'tough on crime' dogma but opposes applying adult sentences to children under 16; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Margaret Talbot's article (Sept. 10) was gripping. As a parent of two teenagers, I found the real-life stories gut-wrenching. How can a civilized society permit the lives of children not yet old enough to drive to be destroyed by a criminal justice system so blindly focused on the deed and not the doer? I support the ''tough on crime'' dogma, but the logic of applying adult sentences to kids under 16 doesn't make sense.</p>
        <p>James A. Messina  Ridgefield, Conn.</p>
      </block>
